Author: Eric Petit <titer@videolan.org>


About libdvdcss

libdvdcss (<http://developers.videolan.org/libdvdcss/> is a part of the VideoLAN project (<http://www.videolan.org/>). It is a simple library designed for accessing DVDs like a block device without having to bother about the decryption. 


About libdvdread

libdvdread is a part of the Ogle project (<http://www.dtek.chalmers.se/groups/dvd/>). It provides a simple foundation for reading DVD video disks. It parses IFO files, reads NAV-blocks, and performs CSS authentication and descrambling using libdvdcss.
